HEADWORD: Antilogous
<hw>An*til"o*gous</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧n*t⟦icr⟧l"⟦osl⟧*g⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Of the contrary name or character; -- opposed to
<ant>analogous</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Antilogous pole</b></col> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld>, <cd>that
pole of a crystal which becomes negatively electrified when
heated.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antilogy</ent>⟦br⟧
